<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-09T13:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-09T13:21:00-05:00" n="842" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6124/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-09T20:00:00+01:39"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                        1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 10—3
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>518. Department’s telegram of January 7, 6 p.m. Have succeeded gaining
                            consent and cooperation in every way for transfer through Hangö. Attacks
                            against Finnish Government sure to result, but to no probable permanent
                            effect. Awaiting definite decision as to Hangö.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Haynes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>